olive oil
1 packet Roasted Pumpkin
½ lemon
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet beef strips
1 sachet Southeast Asian Spice Blend
1 packet garlic paste
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet roasted peanuts

Zap pumpkin until hot and steaming, 2-3 mins.
Slice lemon in half. Chop tomato. Thinly slice cucumber.
Grab a bowl. Combine sweet chilli, a squeeze of lemon juice and a good drizzle of olive oil.

Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat.
Cook beef and spice blend, tossing, until browned, 1-2 mins.
Add a generous drizzle of olive oil and garlic paste and cook until fragrant, 1 min.

Add tomato, cucumber and salad leaves to dressing. Season and toss.
Plate up salad and pumpkin. Top with beef strips.
Scatter over peanuts and serve with remaining lemon wedges.